freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Feeling a little zapped, like a nap would be welcome (rarely do naps).
Note: Feeling a little tired, but also could be from Repatha injection on 3/1. That usually kicks in 3-7 days afterward with muscle aches for a day or two.
Pretty sure aches due to shoveling snow/ice yesterday vs shot 4 days ago. Naproxen calmed it.
Tenderness at injection site and mild flu-like aches/muscles.

Woke up with mild tenderness at injection site, but realized I had been sleeping on my left side/arm (where I got the shot). Once I got up and moving around, it didnt bother me. Also, fell asleep at about 3:30pm (which I never do - take naps), and here it is 6:30 and Im waking up! Definitely dont feel bad tho.
